1 A Little Survey

Here are just a few questions so I can get to know you and so you can get practice submitting an assignment in Canvas. For each question, insert your answer underneath. Make sure each answer is at the minimum a complete sentence with correctly spelled words and correct puncuation. Half the points in this assignment depend on your picture and name being correct!! Be sure to put your photo in the AAA_Owner_Info folder and call it My_photo.jpg after first renaming the current one to Koala.jpg .

1.1 Where are you now?

What row are you in, front,middle or back? Do you usually choose a similiar row in other classes? What is the computer number where you are sitting? How on a scale of 1 to 10 (1=low, 10=high) How you feel about periodic seat re-assignment, say how and why. Teams, have you ever worked on one in a class setting?

I do not currently have a physical seat, we are in a Pandemic called COVID-19 and are attending classes through distance learning. I do however, usually pick the front row in the middle. I need as little distraction as I can get. My Computer is a personal lap top HP. On a scale of 1-10 I’m a 3. I don’t think seat reassignment is necessary in a college setting, however I have been in classes where there are students who are so rude and disrespectful that they will talk to each other while the teacher is teaching with no regard for others or the Professor. Then they need to be treated like the immature children they are acting like and be assigned seats away from the others or get out of class. I have worked with teams a couple of times, and I am not a fan of it. It is hard to group together when you are working and only have time for class participation and you usually get someone on the team who doesn’t participate and it effects your grade.

##Homework Help and Getting around?
On a scale of 1 to 10, where 1 is a total dummy (doesn’t know a mouse from a keyboard) and 10 is a complete geek (knows computer stuff in and out) How do you rate yourself? Do you have a computer you can use at home? If so, what kind is it (windows, Apple, Linux)? Do you have internet access at home?
How do you get to class? Are there issues that limit when you can be at the college?Where and when did you attend high school? Do you currently have a job?

###my answer

I would rate myself a 4 on computer knowledge. Yes, I do have a computer at home to work on. My computer is an HP and came with Windows. However, my main browser I use is Chrome, because a lot of the AVC Canvass assignments work better with Chrome. You have to download a specific app from windows every time you need to do an assignment. Yes,I do have internet at home. If I was meeting in a physical class setting I would drive myself to class, but since we are currently using distance learning, I am able to get onto my classes at home. I attended High School in Miami Florida and graduated in 1982. I currently have a job at a Martial Art Studio. I was previously a front end manager/counselor/driver/cafeteria supervisor/inventory rep…because of COVID-19 we are currently running as a Day Care/School Program for essential workers. I currently am a supervisor/manager.
